-- Chilean Stock Movers: Besalco, E-CL and Lan Airlines Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-05-08T21:01:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/chilean-stock-movers-besalco-e-cl-and-lan-airlines-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  retreated 0.6 percent to 4,520.62. The  MSCI
Chile index  fell 1 percent to 2,549.87.  Besalco SA (BESALCO)   rose 0.7 percent to a one-month
high of 986.61 pesos. The construction company’s first-quarter
profit increased 24 percent to 4.58 billion pesos ($9.4 million)
from a year earlier, according to a statement on the website of
Chile’s securities regulator.  E-CL SA (ECL)   gained 0.6 percent to 1,270 pesos. The
unit of GDF Suez rose after Diario Financiero said Chile’s
billionaire Luksic family may buy a stake in an E-CL project.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   fell 0.9 percent to 13,479 pesos.
 Brazil ’s securities regulator approved Lan’s plan to begin a
tender offer for shares of carrier Tam SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
